INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (1, 'Introduction to SQL', 'SQL is a domain-specific language used in programming and designed for managing data held in a relational database management system.', 'John Doe', '2022-10-01 10:00:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (2, 'Data Manipulation in SQL', 'SQL provides various commands for modifying and processing data in a database.', 'Alice Smith', '2022-10-02 11:30:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (3, 'SQL Joins Explained', 'Joins in SQL are used to combine rows from two or more tables based on a related column between them.', 'Bob Johnson', '2022-10-03 09:45:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (4, 'Query Optimization in SQL', 'Optimizing SQL queries is essential for improving database performance and efficiency.', 'Emma Brown', '2022-10-04 13:15:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (5, 'Advanced SQL Techniques', 'Advanced SQL features like subqueries, triggers, and transactions enhance the functionality of databases.', 'Michael Wilson', '2022-10-05 14:30:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (6, 'Data Modeling with SQL', 'Data modeling in SQL involves designing the structure and relationships of database tables.', 'Sarah Lee', '2022-10-06 12:00:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (7, 'Normalization in Databases', 'Normalization is the process of organizing data in a database to reduce redundancy and improve data integrity.', 'David Garcia', '2022-10-07 10:45:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (8, 'Indexing in SQL', 'Indexes in SQL are used to speed up data retrieval operations by creating a quick lookup structure.', 'Olivia Martinez', '2022-10-08 15:00:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (9, 'SQL Security Best Practices', 'Ensuring security in SQL databases involves measures like encryption, access control, and regular audits.', 'Daniel Adams', '2022-10-09 11:30:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (10, 'SQL Injection Prevention', 'Preventing SQL injection attacks is crucial for safeguarding database data from unauthorized access.', 'Sophia Davis', '2022-10-10 08:30:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (11, 'Database Backup Strategies', 'Implementing reliable backup strategies in SQL databases ensures data recovery in case of failures or disasters.', 'James Taylor', '2022-10-11 14:15:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (12, 'SQL Server Administration', 'Managing SQL Server involves tasks like configuration, monitoring, and performance optimization.', 'Ella Clark', '2022-10-12 16:45:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (13, 'Data Warehousing Concepts', 'Data warehousing in SQL involves storing and managing large volumes of structured data for analysis and reporting.', 'William Brown', '2022-10-13 09:00:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (14, 'SQL Triggers Implementation', 'SQL triggers are special stored procedures that are automatically executed in response to specific events on a table.', 'Ava Johnson', '2022-10-14 10:30:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (15, 'Concurrency Control in SQL', 'Concurrency control mechanisms in SQL databases ensure that multiple transactions can execute concurrently without interference.', 'Logan Martinez', '2022-10-15 12:45:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (16, 'SQL Server Performance Tuning', 'Performance tuning in SQL Server involves optimizing queries, indexes, and server configurations for better speed and efficiency.', 'Grace Miller', '2022-10-16 13:00:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (17, 'Database Security Auditing', 'Regular security auditing of databases helps identify vulnerabilities and ensure compliance with data protection regulations.', 'Henry Wilson', '2022-10-17 15:30:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (18, 'SQL Database Design Principles', 'Designing SQL databases involves defining tables, relationships, and constraints to meet the requirements of an application.', 'Zoe Moore', '2022-10-18 09:15:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (19, 'SQL Server Replication Methods', 'Replication in SQL Server is the process of copying and distributing data from one database to another for scalability and availability.', 'Lucas Brown', '2022-10-19 11:00:00')

INSERT INTO LectureNotes (id, title, content, author, created_at) VALUES (20, 'SQL Reporting Services Overview', 'SQL Reporting Services provide tools for creating, managing, and delivering reports based on data from SQL databases.', 'Nora Anderson', '2022-10-20 14:45:00')
